What is an Embedding?

An embedding is a numerical (vector) representation of text, images, audio, or other data that captures its meaning.

Instead of storing words as plain text, AI converts them into lists of numbers. These numbers preserve semantic meaning, allowing the AI to understand that words and sentences with similar meanings should have similar vectors.

Simple Definition

Embedding = Converting text into numbers while preserving its meaning.

=====

Why Do We Need Embeddings?

Computers cannot understand natural language directly.

For example:

Apple
Banana
Orange

To a computer, these are just characters.

AI first converts them into vectors like:

Apple  → [0.21, -0.45, 0.88, ...]
Banana → [0.24, -0.40, 0.85, ...]
Orange → [0.20, -0.43, 0.90, ...]

These vectors help AI understand that all three are fruits.

