Relating this to your Google Colab project

In your watch chatbot, this line is creating embeddings:

model = SentenceTransformer("all-MiniLM-L6-v2")
embedding = model.encode(text)

Here's what happens:

The watch catalog text is split into chunks.
all-MiniLM-L6-v2 converts each chunk into a 384-dimensional embedding vector.
Those vectors are stored in FAISS.
When a user asks a question, the question is also converted into a 384-dimensional vector.
FAISS compares the vectors and returns the most semantically similar chunks.
Gemini or another LLM uses those chunks to produce a natural-language answer.

This is why embeddings are the foundation of semantic search and RAG systems.

